title: Cavs fall in ITA Championship pre-qualifying
text:
Cavs fall in ITA Championship pre-qualifying FROM STAFF REPORTS The Daily Progress 
PACIFIC PALISADES, Calif. â€” Seniors Maci Epstein and Skylar Morton both fell on the opening day of action at the Riviera ITA All-American Championships at the Riviera Tennis Club on Saturday. 
Epstein fell to Ashvarya Shrivastava of New Mexico State 6-4, 2-6, 7-5 in the opening round of play, while Morton fell to Gabriela Porubin of Wichita State 3-6, 6-3, 6-4. The Cavaliers will continue to be represented at the annual event with the qualifying round. Subscription Required An online service is needed to view this article in its entirety.
